MatchedRegions.transcript: In our experiments, the evaluated UDA methods achieved a maximum accuracy gain of around 4% and high positives and negative rates.
This shows that the methods are not able to achieve comparable results to the supervised baselines.

MatchedRegion.Text: Adaptation methods are not able to achieve comparable results to the supervised baselines (UFLD-TO):

MatchedRegions.transcript: Furthermore, we observe force-positive and force-negative rates increase significantly on the multi-target task of Moulin.

MatchedRegion.Text: FP and FN rates increase significantly on the multi-target task of MuLane

MatchedRegions.transcript: We want to emphasize that force-positive and force-negatives represent strongly detected and missing lanes, which can lead to crucial impacts on autonomous driving.
